{"name": "vizu", "metadata": {"name": "vizu", "version": "0.1.7", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/gedemagt/vizer", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["flask", "pandas", "scipy", "dash", "dash-extensions", "dash-bootstrap-components", "dash-table", "watchdog"], "summary": "Visualization of data files", "upload_time": 1732885225}, "documentation": ["# Vizu - the simple CSV-viewer\n\nDoing advanced analysis of data in CSV-format can be done with many tools - Excel and Pandas are two popular choises.\nHowever, to quickly browse through the data for simple analysis and exploration, you will need more button-clicks than you should. \n\n`vizu` is meant to bridge the gap by providing a simple UI to browse a CSV file.\n\nIt uses the excellent libraries `dash` and `pandas` under the hood for GUI and data manipulation, respectively.\n\n### Installation\n`pip install vizu`\n\n### Browse your first .csv file\nRun the following command in a terminal\n\n`vizu path/to/file.csv`\n\nand go to your browser via the link it outputs.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "vizer.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "vizer.utils.full_width_input", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vizer.utils.create_row", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "label", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "component", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "label_width", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "vizer.workspace", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "vizer.workspace.workspace_from_filename", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vizer.workspace.__getattr__", "asynchronous": false, "params